.\" $Id$
.\" The following macro turns the program name in uppercase letters.
.de uppercase
.  tr aAbBcCdDeEfFgGhHiIjJkKlLmMnNoOpPqQrRsStTuUvVwWxXyYzZ
.  di uppercase
.    nop \\*[\\$1]
.    br
.  di
.  asciify uppercase
.  chop uppercase
.  tr aabbccddeeffgghhiijjkkllmmnnooppqqrrssttuuvvwwxxyyzz
.  ds \\$2 \\*[uppercase]\"
..
.\" Define the program name in its original and uppercase forms.
.ds name gchemcalc@STABILITY@
.uppercase name NAME
.de prog
.  B gchemcalc@STABILITY@
..
.\" Begin manual page.
.TH "\*[NAME]" "1" "@GCU_API_VER@" "gnome-chemistry-utils @VERSION@" "User commands"

.SH "NAME"
\*[name] \- simple calculator for chemists

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.prog
.B [options]
.BI [ formula ]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
.prog
is a simple calculator for chemists.

